The Chrysanthemum fabric collection by Alison Glass for Andover Fabrics is inspired by the Isabella Stewart Gardner Museum in Boston. This week, we will share a bit more about the individual designs that make up the line, shipping in November 2023. First up is 'Folk'! The creatures in 'Folk' are a simple line work interpretation of some of the many animal shapes cast in brass and iron throughout the museum. Found on a variety of objects like candelabras, gates, and vases, the inspiration is endless. Printed in white pigment on top of a geometric design, the ink allows some color from below to come through, giving a magical quality to the print. ⁠
