'Courtyard', the largest design in the Chrysanthemum fabric collection, is inspired by the many velvety wallpapers and floral prints throughout the museum. It is named for the otherworldly four-story atrium in the middle of the building, The Courtyard. Described as the heart and soul of the museum, most of the rooms look out onto The Courtyard, where the floral displays change throughout the year to reflect the seasons. 'Courtyard' is part of the Chrysanthemum fabric collection by Alison Glass for Andover Fabrics, shipping in November 2023.⁠
